1. There was a negative relation between ΔFMD and ΔD-dimer.
2. The β value for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔD-dimer was -22.70.
3. The 95% confidence interval for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔD-dimer was -39.27 to -6.13.
4. The p-value for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔD-dimer was 0.011.
5. There was a negative relation between ΔFMD and ΔCD95+ CD4+ T cells.
6. The β value for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔCD95+ CD4+ T cells was -0.16.
7. The 95% confidence interval for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔCD95+ CD4+ T cells was -0.28 to -0.04.
8. The p-value for the relation between ΔFMD and ΔCD95+ CD4+ T cells was 0.013.
9. The relations were adjusted for age and duration of HIV.
